<dl id="n05035j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05035j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05035j"> 35(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> case of possession</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Directly afterwards, Brice himself came in sight. He was in a fury of rage, and rushing up to the venerable bishop, poured out upon him a torrent of abuse. St. Martin, calm and serene as usual, answered him with tender, soothing words, but to no purpose. The devil had, for the time, completely got the upper hand, and Brice, usually so gay and jaunty, was like one possessed. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 77</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
